1. cs.AI - The paper proposes a framework that uses multi-agent deep reinforcement learning methods to optimize online matching for ride-sourcing services. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence. 
2. cs.LG - The paper uses deep reinforcement learning methods to optimize the matching process, which falls under the category of machine learning. 
3. cs.RO - The paper deals with optimizing the efficiency of a ride-sourcing system, which involves resource allocation and scheduling, falling under the category of robotics. 
4. cs.SY - The paper proposes a framework for optimizing a ride-sourcing system, which involves multiple agents (drivers and passengers) interacting with each other, falling under the category of systems and control. 
5. cs.CE - The paper proposes a framework for optimizing the efficiency of a ride-sourcing system, which involves designing and implementing algorithms for resource allocation and scheduling, falling under the category of computational engineering.
